INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (89,1,'2010-05-06 10:39:54','2010-05-06 09:39:54','<strong>Get the start page PageReference:</strong>\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">PageReference.StartPage</pre>\r\nA PageRefernce is basically a wrapper for integer ids. It also containsÂ convenienceÂ methods as in the above example which simply gets the start page id from the configuration:\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">EPiServer.Configuration.Settings.Instance.PageStartId</pre>\r\nThe PageData class holds information about the page such as name and URL. It makes pageÂ propertiesÂ available through the property \"Property\" (PropertyDataCollection).\r\n\r\n<strong>Get PageData from a PageReference:</strong>\r\n<pre class=\"brush:csharp\">DataFactory.Instance.GetPage(PageReference.StartPage)</pre>','EPiServer Snippets','','publish','open','open','','episerver-snippets','','','2010-05-06 16:56:06','2010-05-06 15:56:06','',0,'http://www.jonathansewell.co.uk/?p=89',0,'post','',0);
